1
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:08,560
Marshal, Ambassador Johnson says

2
00:00:08,560 --> 00:00:09,690
Rose has been found.

3
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:11,520
But she was killed by his men.

4
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:13,080
The man who killed her is dead too.

5
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:14,160
His throat was slit.

6
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:15,560
What about the contract?

7
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:18,330
They didn't find the contract on Rose.

8
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:23,880
Regarding seeing Yao Shengsheng at the hotel,

9
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:25,970
don't let the Ambassador find out.

10
00:00:26,040 --> 00:00:27,800
If anyone dares to leak this,

11
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:29,480
kill them.

12
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:31,960
Also,

13
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:35,880
find out what Yao Shengsheng has been up to recently.

14
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:36,410
Yes, sir.

15
00:00:44,880 --> 00:00:47,140
As long as I cover the real gunshot wound,

16
00:00:47,280 --> 00:00:49,000
and keep it bleeding,

17
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:51,980
I should be able to fool Song Huainan for now.

18
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:35,800
Brother, I saw the military doctor come in.

19
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:36,560
Are you sick?

20
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:37,680
I'm fine.

21
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:39,479
Your sister-in-law is hurt.

22
00:01:39,479 --> 00:01:41,340
I called the doctor to take a look.

23
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:51,400
Mrs. Song's wound

24
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,530
looks very serious.

25
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:55,000
But I really couldn't tell

26
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,729
what sharp weapon caused this.

27
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:57,880
It's turning green.

28
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:58,840
It really looks like it was tainted by

29
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,970
something unclean.

30
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,800
Something unclean?

31
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:04,440
Is it poison?

32
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:07,440
It's hard to say if it's poison yet.

33
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:14,050
Shengsheng,

34
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:17,020
do you remember how the robber

35
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:18,000
hurt you?

36
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:21,480
I...

37
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,490
I was so scared that day.

38
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:27,160
I just remember someone

39
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,130
rushing at me looking vicious.

40
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,960
Then he had

41
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,920
something dark and filthy in his hand,

42
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:35,120
and he stabbed at me.

43
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:40,680
Doctor, am I really poisoned?

44
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:41,650
Marshal.

45
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,620
Let me check again.

46
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:48,240
Military doctor, check carefully again

47
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,600
to see if my sister-in-law is poisoned.

48
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,920
We need to know what poison it is

49
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,400
so we can treat her.

50
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,920
If it were poison,

51
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:55,660
after a whole night...

52
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,840
Toxins would spread,

53
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,920
but right now,

54
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,920
there are no signs of that.

55
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:03,920
So, does that mean

56
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:05,960
she wasn't poisoned?

57
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:06,900
Precisely.

58
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:13,720
Treat my wife's wounds first.

59
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:14,930
Yes, sir.

60
00:03:27,079 --> 00:03:28,600
Madam, I'm sorry.

61
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:30,240
I misunderstood you.

62
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:38,079
Get some rest.

63
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:40,340
I'll see the military doctor out.

64
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:57,480
Are you okay?

65
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:01,160
There was poison in that bullet.

66
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:02,480
I don't know if we fooled

67
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:03,740
that military doctor.

68
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,040
Don't worry.

69
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:06,840
Leave it to me.

70
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:09,020
Just focus on recovering.

71
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:18,959
Just in case,

72
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:20,320
take this back to the lab

73
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:21,519
and check for poison.

74
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,040
Yes, Marshal.

75
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,560
Tell me as soon as the results are out.

76
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:27,160
Remember,

77
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,080
no one else must know about this.

78
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:47,200
I need to find an antidote quickly.

79
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,159
Otherwise,

80
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:50,130
I'm afraid I'll really die.

81
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:15,320
Miss.

82
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,720
Miss, you're finally awake.

83
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,080
Where am I?

84
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,400
This is my silk shop.

85
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:46,560
I saw you faint outside,

86
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:47,820
so I brought you in.

87
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,220
Thank you, sir.

88
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,080
You're welcome, Miss.

89
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,320
Have some water.

90
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:05,680
Sir, what incense is this?

91
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:08,840
It smells gentle and soothing. It's quite unique.

92
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:10,200
My wife made it.

93
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,930
I don't know what kind it is.

94
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:15,520
I won't impose any longer.

95
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:17,040
You don't look well.

96
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,480
Shall I call a rickshaw

97
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,410
to take you back?

98
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:21,160
No need. Thank you, Boss.

99
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,520
I'll come back another day

100
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:23,840
to thank you properly.

101
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:28,300
Take care then.

102
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:35,880
I found some information on Aunt Hong.

103
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:36,860
Take a look.

104
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,600
This Aunt Hong

105
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,520
is an expert in incense.

106
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:44,360
Rare incense like Yuelin and Fengsui

107
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:45,480
are nothing to her.

108
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,980
Father has always loved incense.

109
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,920
I know the scent of Yuelin Incense.

110
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:54,650
It smells exactly the same as in the room just now.

111
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:57,560
The boss's wife and Aunt Hong,

112
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:59,440
could they be connected?

113
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:19,800
Song, forget about the lost contract.

114
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,700
We'll stop looking for it.

115
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,800
You should know that the contract

116
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,240
contains the terms for the land sale.

117
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,960
How can you get the land without the contract?

118
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:30,080
I've already acquired the land successfully.

119
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:31,920
The spices have already been planted,

120
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:34,520
so the contract isn't that important anymore.

121
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:37,260
But if we can't find the contract,

122
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:39,600
and someone uses it against us,

123
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,640
the Song family's reputation will be ruined.

124
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:45,370
I didn't expect that given Marshal Song's power,

125
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:46,840
finding a single contract

126
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:48,240
would be this difficult.

127
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:51,680
And that dancer definitely wasn't acting alone.

128
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,600
My men must have been killed by her accomplice.

129
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:58,040
Can't Commander Song find any clues at all?

130
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,060
I've got all the materials ready.

131
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:09,880
When will Mr. Yao's soap factory

132
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,320
start production?

133
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:13,520
Time is money, Song.

134
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,160
I don't need you to tell me what to do.

135
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:29,640
Traitor!

136
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,320
Extra! Extra!

137
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:34,120
The Songs are colluding with foreigners!

138
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:34,980
Give me a paper.

139
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:35,799
Traitor!

140
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:36,850
I'll take three.

141
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,080
One for me too.

142
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:38,960
Me too.

143
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:39,919
Give me one.

144
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:40,520
Let me see.

145
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,000
This is too much.

146
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:42,960
What on earth is this?

147
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:43,960
It's outrageous!

148
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:45,920
The Song family is betraying the country.

149
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,360
How dare they publish such news?

150
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,820
I think they want their newspaper shut down.

151
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:54,240
Investigate! Find out who is behind this.

152
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,280
Drag them all out.

153
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:55,810
Yes, sir.

154
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:06,200
It's me.

155
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,240
That look...

156
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,040
I thought you were Song Huainan.

157
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:11,680
The Song family has been cracking down too hard lately.

158
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:12,800
My friend at the newspaper office

159
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,280
reported that the Song family are traitors,

160
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,480
and ran away immediately.

161
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,480
If he hadn't left,

162
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,940
he was bound to get caught.

163
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:20,010
There's one more thing.

164
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:22,040
At a silk shop,

165
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:23,860
I smelled Yuelin Incense.

166
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,080
Yuelin Incense?

167
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:28,240
That incense is extremely hard to make.

168
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:35,970
When I investigated Aunt Hong before, she was good at making it.

169
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,160
I slipped up.

170
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:42,240
I always thought she had left,

171
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:44,400
so my investigation went in the wrong direction.

172
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:46,660
I forgot there was another possibility.

173
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,600
What if she never left?

174
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:51,240
Then follow this clue

175
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,360
and investigate again

176
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:53,360
to see if it's her.

177
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:55,360
I'll go right now.

178
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:03,320
There is a sip left. Finish it before you go.

179
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:05,800
Go now.

180
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,480
Whoever pays is the boss.

181
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,200
Do you know each other?

182
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:31,760
Shengsheng? Why is it you?

183
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,120
Mrs. Song's wound

184
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:34,250
looks very serious,

185
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:36,720
but I really can't tell

186
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,320
what sharp weapon caused it.

187
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,610
It's turning green.

188
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:42,200
I can't be sure yet if it's poison.
